  "text": "Analysis of the ability to detect changes in cognitive and mobility skills has demonstrated the possibility of predicting a decline or an improvement in a person's mobility as measured by the Arm Curl test. This not only confirms the results of the previous RCI analysis, where we saw that reliable changes in the Arm Curl tests were detectable by smart home activitylabeled data but also adds value to the results suggesting that the direction of the change is also predictable. Literature also supports the idea of the relationship between Arm Curl test scores and ADLs [CITATION_1] . This finding may prove useful not only to monitor the progress of a disorder like dementia but also to closely examine individuals who are undergoing rehabilitation.",
